events.name: Learn to Implement ML Algorithms in our Machine Learning Study Jam
events.description:
• What we'll do
New to Machine Learning but don’t know where to start? Join us for a Machine Learning Study Jam where we will run through the Machine Learning Crash Course (MLCC)!

This course is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable you to use machine learning in your everyday projects and learn about the power of TensorFlow. This is a great opportunity for anyone with basic technical knowledge and limited Machine Learning knowledge willing to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

**Bring your laptop!**

Agenda:
12PM: event start
12:30PM: overview & first 3 modules of MLCC
2:15PM: break
2:30PM: TensorFlow modules
4:00PM: event end

• What to bring
Laptops

• Important to know

events.name: Join us at the TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018 Extended Viewing Party
events.description:
• What we'll do
TensorFlow Dev Summit brings together a diverse mix of machine learning users from around the world for a full day of highly technical talks, demos, and conversation with the TensorFlow team and community.

It is no question that machine learning is one of the hottest and one of the most important technology topics for developers and we think you can use this as an opportunity to build local machine learning communities or engage with your local machine learning users.

The TensorFlow Dev Summit will happen on the Friday before our event, so we will view the keynote of the event, and then try our hands on a codelab. We will also discuss one or two machine learning datasets.

We will also try our hands on one of the labs from the Machine Learning Study Jam.

• What to bring
Laptops

• Important to know

A Google I/O extended (https://events.google.com/io/extended/) event is an extension of the event, a great opportunity to get together, chat, listen to the keynotes, discuss further. Google I/O Extended are taking place across the globe, at the same time or around the time of Google I/O.

events.name: Google Cloud IoT
events.description:
Google Cloud IoT is a complete set of tools to connect, process, store, and analyze data both at the edge and in the cloud. The platform consists of scalable, fully-managed cloud services; an integrated software stack for edge/on-premises computing with machine learning capabilities, and managed Android Things OS for all your IoT needs.

This event will be hosted by Nnamdi Judges, who has been working with sensors and embedded devices for a while.

events.name: Next '18 Extended Kaduna
events.description:

Attendees to this event will get one month free of Qwiklabs to take a quest on Machine Learning or Cloud Architecture. Anyone who completes one quest will get a second month free!

Attendees will also get one month free of Coursera access to one of five specializations offered by Google Cloud.

events.name: Cloud Study Jams - Using BigQuery for Machine Learning
events.description:
Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud technologies as a team.
Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with using BigQuery for Machine Learning.
After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

What to bring:
Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

events.name: Women Techmakers Kaduna: Meet & Greet
events.description:
Google's Women Techmakers program provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology.
The WTM Kaduna Meet & Greet is an avenue for the members of the community to know themselves better, learn from one another and understand our individual tech needs in order to plan activities around these moving forward.

Expectations:
- Meet with other women from the community.

- M n M Ice breaker

- Share our stories: How did we get here? Our challenges, victories and the journey so far?

- Share our tech interests and find people with similar interests.

- What do we want to learn in 2020? [Android, Web, Data, Design]

Customized programs will be developed for the WTM Kaduna Community in 2020 as a result of this activity.

events.name: Study Jam (SSA)
events.description: In this introductory-level quest, you will get hands-on practice with the Google Cloud Platform’s fundamental tools and services. GCP Essentials is the recommended first Quest for the Google Cloud learner—you will come in with little or no prior cloud knowledge, and come out with practical experience that you can apply to your first GCP project. From writing Cloud Shell commands and deploying your first virtual machine, to running applications on Kubernetes Engine or with load balancing, GCP Essentials is a prime introduction to the platform’s basic features.

events.name: Study Jam - SSA Francophone GDGs
events.description:
Dans cette quête de niveau débutant, vous allez vous familiariser avec les outils et services fondamentaux de la plate-forme Google Cloud.

Le GCP Essentials est la première quête recommandée pour l'apprenant Google Cloud; vous commencez avec peu de connaissances préalables en matière de cloud et vous terminez avec une expérience pratique que vous pourriez appliquer à votre premier projet GCP.

De l’écriture des commandes Cloud Shell au déploiement de votre première machine virtuelle, à l’exécution des applications sur le Kubernetes Engine avec la gestion de la montée en charge, GCP Essentials est une introduction primordiale aux fonctions de base de la plateforme Google Cloud..

Merci de regarder cette vidéo:

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLIivdWyY5sqK6aqu4Dmo9lIsZ8Ns_LsyC

events.name: Visualizing Sensor Data with Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
events.description:
Ever wondered how to stream sensor data to a cloud dashboard?.

Join us as we collect real-life ambient data (temperature and pressure), ingest the data to Google Cloud Platform (GCP), and display the data on a live dashboard.

We shall be making use of several GCP technologies; Cloud IoT Core, Pub/Sub, Dataflow, BigQuery, and Data Studio.

events.name: Flutter Interact: Viewing Party
events.description:
Flutter is Google’s UI toolkit for building beautiful, natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop from a single codebase.

On the 11th of December 2019, they'll be a major Flutter event tagged "Flutter Interact". The event will be hosted in Brooklyn, NewYork and broadcasted to a global audience.

This event will showcase the latest from Google Design and Flutter, Google’s free and open source UI toolkit to build beautiful, natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop - all from a single codebase

On the 14th of December 2019, GDG Cloud Kaduna will be hosting the Flutter Interact: Viewing Party. Here are the agendas lined up for the event;

1. A viewing party where attendees will watch the Flutter Interact event video recordings with community members.

2. Talks by local speakers

3. Flutter Codelabs

upcoming.name: Women Techmakers Kaduna: IWD 2020
upcoming.description:
Google's Women Techmakers program provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology.
The WTM Kaduna International Women's day draws from the global IWD theme which is about 'Collective Individualism.'

Our IWD celebration will serve as an avenue for the members of the community to come together and have conversations that'll help drive this goal.
We are all parts of a whole. Our individual actions, conversations, behaviors, and mindsets can have an impact on our larger society. Collectively, we can make change happen. Collectively, we can each help to create a gender-equal world.

We can all choose to be #EachforEqual.
